          <link xlink:href="pubmed:11875461"/>
          <link xlink:href="pubmed:18568041"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>Cyt_c represents the release of cytochrome c from the mitochondria.

Ow YP, Green DR, Hao Z, Mak TW. Nat Rev Mol Cell Biol. 2008
Cyt c is localized in the mitochondrial intermembrane space and is part of the mitochondrial electron transport chain .
pubmed: 18568041

Karin M, Lin A. Nat Immunol. 2002
Cytochrome c is released when cardiolipin, to which it is attached, is oxidized
pubmed: 11875461
</comment>
      </annotation>
